	(13, 1, '2012-06-17 09:32:11', '2012-06-17 09:32:11', '<img title="Packing-1" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-1-433x6505.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_0"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, I want to apologize for the spelling mistakes and grammar errors in advance.Â  MM and I had the brilliant idea of not sleeping before heading to the airport at 5:45 am to catch our flights.Â  By 4 am, I had a mini outer body experience where I wasnât sure how to get water from the refrigerator.Â  And then the million dollar question â water or juice?Â  After a few minutes with an empty glass on hand, I poured some juice, topped it off with water, took a sip, and put the glass in the refrigerator.Â  The whole time, I had no idea what I was doing.Â  Again, I apologize if this blog post makes little sense.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-2" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-2-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_1"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhen flying, I like to be as comfortable as possible.Â  For short distances, I donât mind wearing jeans, but for long flights, I tend to opt for sweatpants or soft cotton maxi dresses.Â  I feel more free and nonrestrictive, which helps make the overall flying experience more pleasant.Â  Also knowing that Florence will be around 85 degrees when I get there, I can just take off my jacket and be weather appropriate when I land.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-3" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-3-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_2"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n:: Packing Segment ::\r\n\r\nFor this trip, I knew I needed to check in luggage, so my goal was to maximize as many outfits as possible into my suitcase.Â  I packed about 16 outfits, 6 pairs of shoes, 4 handbags (one of which Iâm carrying on the flight), a few belts, 2 watches, and my usual wristwear.Â  With that said, you probably wouldnât believe me when I say Iâm a light packer.\r\n\r\nA few weeks ago, Luisa Via Roma invited me to participate in theirÂ <a href="http://firenze4ever.luisaviaroma.com/" target="_blank">Firenze4Ever</a>Â styling event.Â  When I got the email, I read it a dozen time making sure it wasnât spam.Â  I was beyond thrilled and am still in disbelief.Â  Iâve never been to Florence before and was in complete shock just thinking about the trip.Â  And since weâre going to be in Italy for a few days, MM and I decided to film a creative video while weâre there.Â  In addition to my travel outfits, Iâm actually packing pairings for the video as well, thus the unusual high number of outfits.Â  Everything that I brought is summer appropriate, so if youâre heading to a super warm location this year, I hope my outfit suggestions are helpful =)\r\n\r\nWhen I pack, I tend to separate day and night outfits.Â  Since the weather is going to be in the mid to upper 80â²s during the day, I brought shift dress, shorts, skirts, and sleeveless tops.Â  I love wearing shift dresses, because theyâre low maintenance and are quick to transition from day to night by simply adding heels.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-12" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-12-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_3"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShorts and skirts are my best friends in super warm weather.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-7" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-7-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_4"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI also packed a few dresses for night events.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-4" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-4-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_5"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSince weâre going to do a lot of walking, I brought sandals, flats, and wedges for daywear.Â  And for night events, I packed two pairs of heels.Â  I try my very best to take care of my shoes by stuffing and wrapping them with tissue paper and putting them in their boxes, so they wonât get damaged during the flights.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-8" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-8-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_6"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAll of my handbags are stuffed and in their dust bags.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-6" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-6-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_7"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-16" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-16-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_8"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProtecting my accessories with a travel size jewelry holder.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-5" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-5-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_9"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor all of my delicate dresses and items, I sandwich two large white tissue paper sheets and roll them into a sushi roll to protect them from rubbing.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-9" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-9-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_10"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-15" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-15-650x4332.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_11"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor blazers, I turn one of the arms inside out and fold it into the other arm to keep its shape.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-10" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-10-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_12"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-11" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-11-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_13"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEverything laid outâ¦\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-13" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-13-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_14"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd packed into one luggageâ¦\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-14" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-14-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_15"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNo carry-on needed. Â Olive sitting pretty and ready to go! Â =)\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-17" src="http://www.elodika.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-17-433x6502.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_16"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThank you so much for letting me share my travel/packing segment with you!Â  I hope it was helpful.Â  And moreover, thank you for being on this journey with me.Â  A few years ago while sitting at my desk analyzing financial statements, I never ever thought I would get a chance to travel to Italy for a fashion related event.Â  Sitting here on the plane, I still canât believe it.Â  Thank you for your support and encouragement.Â  I truly appreciate it.Â  I hope youâre having a wonderful weekend so far and talk to you soon!\r\n\r\n:: Outfit ::\r\n\r\nMaxi dress :: Forever 21 (old) (similarÂ <a href="http://rstyle.me/hddsb4d7ie" target="_blank">here</a>)\r\nJacket :: Zara (similarÂ <a href="http://rstyle.me/ftmqdkd7ie" target="_blank">here</a>)\r\nBag :: Celine\r\nShoes ::Â <a href="http://rstyle.me/hwx4qbd7ie" target="_blank">Sam Edelman\r\n</a>Accessories ::Â <a href="http://www.bcbg.com/product/index.jsp?productId=12789734&amp;cp=2769196.2770117&amp;clickid=cat_leftnav_txt&amp;parentPage=family" target="_blank">BCBG</a>Â belt,Â <a href="http://shop.stelladot.com/style/b2c_en_us/shop/necklaces/necklaces-all/la-coco-curb-chain.html" target="_blank">Stella &amp; Dot</a>Â necklace\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Up in the Air :