	(24, 1, '2012-06-17 09:33:47', '2012-06-17 09:33:47', '<img title="Packing-1" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-1-433x650.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_0"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-1-433x650.jpg&amp;description=Up%20in%20the%20Air%20::%20Comfy%20maxi%20dress%20&amp;layout=horizontal" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="320" height="240"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, I want to apologize for the spelling mistakes and grammar errors in advance.Â  MM and I had the brilliant idea of not sleeping before heading to the airport at 5:45 am to catch our flights.Â  By 4 am, I had a mini outer body experience where I wasnât sure how to get water from the refrigerator.Â  And then the million dollar question â water or juice?Â  After a few minutes with an empty glass on hand, I poured some juice, topped it off with water, took a sip, and put the glass in the refrigerator.Â  The whole time, I had no idea what I was doing.Â  Again, I apologize if this blog post makes little sense.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-2" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-2-433x650.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_1"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-2-433x650.jpg&amp;description=Up%20in%20the%20Air%20::%20Comfy%20maxi%20dress%20&amp;layout=horizontal" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="320" height="240"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhen flying, I like to be as comfortable as possible.Â  For short distances, I donât mind wearing jeans, but for long flights, I tend to opt for sweatpants or soft cotton maxi dresses.Â  I feel more free and nonrestrictive, which helps make the overall flying experience more pleasant.Â  Also knowing that Florence will be around 85 degrees when I get there, I can just take off my jacket and be weather appropriate when I land.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-3" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-3-433x650.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_2"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-3-433x650.jpg&amp;description=Up%20in%20the%20Air%20::%20Comfy%20maxi%20dress%20&amp;layout=horizontal" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="320" height="240"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n:: Packing Segment ::\r\n\r\nFor this trip, I knew I needed to check in luggage, so my goal was to maximize as many outfits as possible into my suitcase.Â  I packed about 16 outfits, 6 pairs of shoes, 4 handbags (one of which Iâm carrying on the flight), a few belts, 2 watches, and my usual wristwear.Â  With that said, you probably wouldnât believe me when I say Iâm a light packer.\r\n\r\nA few weeks ago, Luisa Via Roma invited me to participate in theirÂ <a href="http://firenze4ever.luisaviaroma.com/" target="_blank">Firenze4Ever</a>Â styling event.Â  When I got the email, I read it a dozen time making sure it wasnât spam.Â  I was beyond thrilled and am still in disbelief.Â  Iâve never been to Florence before and was in complete shock just thinking about the trip.Â  And since weâre going to be in Italy for a few days, MM and I decided to film a creative video while weâre there.Â  In addition to my travel outfits, Iâm actually packing pairings for the video as well, thus the unusual high number of outfits.Â  Everything that I brought is summer appropriate, so if youâre heading to a super warm location this year, I hope my outfit suggestions are helpful =)\r\n\r\nWhen I pack, I tend to separate day and night outfits.Â  Since the weather is going to be in the mid to upper 80â²s during the day, I brought shift dress, shorts, skirts, and sleeveless tops.Â  I love wearing shift dresses, because theyâre low maintenance and are quick to transition from day to night by simply adding heels.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-12" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-12-650x433.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_3"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-12-650x433.jpg&amp;description=Up%20in%20the%20Air%20::%20Comfy%20maxi%20dress%20&amp;layout=horizontal" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="320" height="240"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShorts and skirts are my best friends in super warm weather.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-7" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-7-650x433.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="433" />\r\n<div id="pinit_4"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-7-650x433.jpg&amp;description=Up%20in%20the%20Air%20::%20Comfy%20maxi%20dress%20&amp;layout=horizontal" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="320" height="240"></iframe></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI also packed a few dresses for night events.\r\n\r\n<img title="Packing-4" src="http://www.wendyslookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/Packing-4-433x650.jpg" alt="" width="433" height="650" />\r\n<div id="pinit_5"><iframe src="http://pinit-cdn.pinterest.com/pinit.html?url=http://www.wendyslookbook.com/2012/06/up-in-the-air-comfy-maxi-dress-packing-segment/&amp;media=h